# VID fetch-CDC invariant (AGENT.md §6, README Tier 2) — the property the vid proof cuts.
# Proves Vid.pulse_sync is no-loss + no-spurious (one req per req0) for ALL clk/pclk phase
# interleavings and ALL reachable states, by k-induction (yosys-smtbmc -i / z3) — unbounded.
# This script is only the yosys PREP that emits the SMT problem; Yosys_equiv.run_proof then
# runs `yosys-smtbmc -i -s z3 -t <depth>` on the result (the ~smtbmc step). Placeholders (named
# WITHOUT braces here — substitution is blind): ours = our emitted gate; monitor =
# vid_invariant.v (the wrapper adding the assumptions + assertions); top = vid_invariant;
# smt2 = the harness-supplied output path.
read_verilog {ours}
read_verilog -formal {monitor}
prep -top {top}
# the emitted gate's FFs have no reset (the design free-runs); pin their formal init to 0 = the
# power-on state, else the solver starts them arbitrary and reports a spurious step-0 trace
setundef -init -zero
# model the multiclock design as a global-clock formal problem for the solver
clk2fflogic
write_smt2 -wires {smt2}
